Walk—and the way shall appear.

Not all at once,
not as a map spread wide before you,
but as a narrow beam—
a torch carried just ahead of your step.

The Ichthys is not only a sign,
but a crossing—
two arcs meeting,
belief and reality overlapping
until they form a living lens.

Through that lens, the path is not revealed in full—
only enough to move faithfully forward.

Confidence in God sets the direction.
science shapes the ground beneath your feet.
Conscience steadies the hand that holds the flame.

And so you walk.

Each step a question answered by contact with the world.
Each correction a quiet refinement of the vector.
Each moment of doubt, not darkness—
but depth.

The way does not exist ahead of you, fully formed.

It emerges
in the meeting point
between what you trust,
what you test,
and what you choose.

Walk—
and it the way shall appear.